<%# app/views/trust_center/docs/dpa-full.html.erb %>

<div class="trust-doc">
  <div class="trust-doc-header">
    <div class="trust-doc-breadcrumb">
      <%= link_to "Trust Center", trust_center_path, class: "trust-doc-breadcrumb-link" %>
      <span class="trust-doc-breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
      <span class="trust-doc-breadcrumb-current">Data Processing Addendum (DPA)</span>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-title-row">
      <%= image_tag "logo", class: "trust-doc-logo", alt: "Workplace.io" %>
      <div class="trust-doc-title">Data Processing Addendum (DPA)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-subtitle">
      This Data Processing Addendum (“DPA”) forms part of the agreement between the Customer and 5 Voices Inc. for Workplace.io where the Customer
      is a Controller and 5 Voices Inc. acts as a Processor of Personal Data on behalf of the Customer.
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-updated">
      Version / Effective date: <%= @trust_center_stamp %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="trust-doc-body">
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">1. Parties</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        This DPA is entered into by and between:
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Customer</strong> (as identified in the Order Form, subscription, or other agreement governing the Service) (“Customer”); and</li>
        <li><strong>5 Voices Inc.</strong>, a Delaware corporation (“Company,” “5 Voices,” or “Processor”).</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        This DPA applies to the extent Company processes Personal Data on behalf of Customer in connection with Customer’s use of Workplace.io (the “Service”).
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">2. Definitions</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Capitalized terms not defined in this DPA have the meaning given in the agreement governing the Service (the “Agreement”).
        The following terms apply:
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>“Controller”</strong>, <strong>“Processor”</strong>, <strong>“Personal Data”</strong>, and <strong>“Processing”</strong> have the meanings given in applicable Data Protection Laws.</li>
        <li><strong>“Data Protection Laws”</strong> means applicable privacy and data protection laws and regulations, including (where applicable) the GDPR, UK GDPR, and Swiss data protection laws.</li>
        <li><strong>“GDPR”</strong> means Regulation (EU) 2016/679.</li>
        <li><strong>“UK GDPR”</strong> means the GDPR as incorporated into UK law.</li>
        <li><strong>“Security Incident”</strong> means a breach of security leading to accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorized disclosure of, or access to Personal Data processed by Company on behalf of Customer.</li>
        <li><strong>“Subprocessor”</strong> means a third party authorized under this DPA to process Personal Data on behalf of Company for the Service.</li>
        <li><strong>“Standard Contractual Clauses”</strong> or <strong>“SCCs”</strong> means the standard contractual clauses approved for cross-border transfers under applicable law.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">3. Roles and scope of processing</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        The parties acknowledge that, for Personal Data processed under this DPA, Customer is the Controller and Company is the Processor.
        Company will process Personal Data only on documented instructions from Customer as set out in this DPA, the Agreement, and Customer’s
        configuration and use of the Service.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Customer instructions:</strong> Customer’s documented instructions include the Agreement, this DPA, and Customer’s configuration and use of the Service.</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Each party will comply with its obligations under applicable Data Protection Laws.</li>
        <li><strong>Details of Processing:</strong> The subject matter, duration, nature and purpose of processing, and types of Personal Data are described in <strong>Appendix A</strong>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">4. Customer obligations</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Customer is responsible for: (a) determining the lawful basis for Processing, (b) providing required notices to data subjects,
        (c) obtaining any required consents, and (d) ensuring its instructions comply with applicable law.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Authorization:</strong> Customer represents it has the authority to provide Personal Data to Company for Processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Configuration:</strong> Customer is responsible for configuring access controls, integrations, and governance settings in a manner consistent with its policies and applicable law.</li>
        <li><strong>Data minimization:</strong> Customer should avoid configuring the Service for individual surveillance or other prohibited uses.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">5. Company obligations</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Company will:
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li>Process Personal Data only on documented instructions from Customer, unless required by law (in which case Company will notify Customer unless prohibited).</li>
        <li>Ensure persons authorized to process Personal Data are subject to confidentiality obligations.</li>
        <li>Implement appropriate technical and organizational measures as described in <strong>Appendix B</strong>.</li>
        <li>Assist Customer as set out in this DPA, including with data subject requests and Security Incident response.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">6. Confidentiality</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Company ensures that persons authorized to process Personal Data have committed themselves to confidentiality or are under an appropriate statutory obligation of confidentiality.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">7. Security measures</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Company will implement and maintain appropriate technical and organizational measures designed to protect Personal Data against a Security Incident.
        Company’s current measures are described in <strong>Appendix B</strong> (Security Measures). Company may update these measures over time provided
        they do not materially degrade the overall security of the Service.
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Security Overview →", trust_doc_path("security-overview"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Encryption →", trust_doc_path("encryption"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Access Controls →", trust_doc_path("access-controls"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">8. Subprocessors</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Customer provides a general authorization for Company to engage Subprocessors to process Personal Data for the Service.
        Company will maintain an up-to-date list of Subprocessors and will impose data protection obligations on Subprocessors consistent with this DPA.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>List:</strong> Company’s current Subprocessors are listed at <%= link_to "Subprocessors", trust_doc_path("subprocessors"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>.</li>
        <li><strong>Notification:</strong> Company will update the Subprocessors list when Subprocessors change. If Customer requires formal notice (e.g., 30 days), Customer may request it in writing.</li>
        <li><strong>Objections:</strong> Customer may object to a new Subprocessor on reasonable data protection grounds by providing written notice within a reasonable time. The parties will work in good faith to resolve the objection.</li>
        <li><strong>Liability:</strong> Company remains responsible for Subprocessors’ performance of their obligations to the extent required by law.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">9. Data subject requests</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Taking into account the nature of processing, Company will assist Customer by appropriate technical and organizational measures, insofar as possible,
        for the fulfilment of Customer’s obligation to respond to requests for exercising data subject rights under Data Protection Laws.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Customer-controlled data:</strong> Where requests relate to workplace collaboration data under Customer control, Customer is responsible for verifying the requester and instructions.</li>
        <li><strong>Assistance:</strong> Company will provide reasonable assistance consistent with the Service and the parties’ agreement, and may charge reasonable fees for excessive or repetitive requests.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "GDPR & Data Rights →", trust_doc_path("gdpr"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">10. Security Incidents</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Company will notify Customer without undue delay after becoming aware of a Security Incident involving Personal Data processed under this DPA.
        Company will provide information reasonably requested by Customer to support Customer’s notification and compliance obligations.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Contents of notice:</strong> where feasible, description of the incident, likely consequences, and measures taken or proposed to address it.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer cooperation:</strong> Customer agrees to coordinate external communications and regulatory notifications unless otherwise required by law.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Incident Response →", trust_doc_path("incident-response"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">11. Audits and compliance information</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Company will make available to Customer information reasonably necessary to demonstrate compliance with this DPA. Where Customer requests audits,
        the parties will cooperate in good faith to agree the scope, timing, and confidentiality protections. Company may satisfy audit requests through
        appropriate documentation and summaries. Company is working toward formal assurance attestations (e.g., SOC 2) but is not currently attested unless
        explicitly stated in writing by Company.
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-callout trust-doc-callout--note">
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-title">Practical approach</div>
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-text">
          Most customer reviews are satisfied through Trust Center documentation, questionnaire responses (e.g., CAIQ-aligned), and subprocessor transparency.
          Contact us to coordinate your review requirements.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "CSA CAIQ →", trust_doc_path("caiq"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "SOC 2 →", trust_doc_path("soc2"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">12. Return or deletion of Personal Data</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        At the end of the provision of Services, Company will, at Customer’s choice and upon request, delete or return Personal Data processed under this DPA,
        unless retention is required by law. Deletion will occur within a reasonable time, subject to technical limitations (including backups).
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Short-lived content:</strong> message content is processed briefly and then removed; derived metadata may be retained to support reporting until deletion is requested or the Agreement ends.</li>
        <li><strong>Backups:</strong> backup copies may persist for a limited period consistent with reasonable operational practices and will be protected and eventually overwritten in the normal course.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Data Handling & Retention →", trust_doc_path("data-handling"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">13. International transfers</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Where Data Protection Laws require a transfer mechanism for international transfers of Personal Data (e.g., from the EEA/UK/Switzerland to the United States or another jurisdiction),
        the parties will implement an appropriate mechanism, such as SCCs, incorporated into this DPA or executed separately.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>SCCs:</strong> where applicable, SCCs will be made available and incorporated by reference or executed as needed.</li>
        <li><strong>Subprocessors:</strong> Company will flow down transfer obligations to Subprocessors where required.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "International Transfers (SCCs) →", trust_doc_path("scc"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">14. Liability</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Liability arising out of or related to this DPA will be subject to the liability limitations and exclusions in the Agreement,
        unless Data Protection Laws require otherwise.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">15. Order of precedence</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        In the event of a conflict between this DPA and the Agreement regarding the processing of Personal Data, this DPA will control to the extent of that conflict.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">16. Contact</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        To request signatures, SCCs, or additional documentation, contact us at:
        <a class="trust-doc-link" href="mailto:security@workplace.io">security@workplace.io</a>.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">17. Signature blocks</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        This DPA may be executed electronically and in counterparts.
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-callout trust-doc-callout--note">
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-title">Customer</div>
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-text">
          Legal Name: _______________________________<br>
          Authorized Signatory: _______________________<br>
          Title: _____________________________________<br>
          Date: ______________________________________
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-callout trust-doc-callout--note">
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-title">5 Voices Inc.</div>
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-text">
          Authorized Signatory: _______________________<br>
          Title: _____________________________________<br>
          Date: ______________________________________
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================= -->
    <!-- APPENDIX A: Details of Processing -->
    <!-- ============================= -->
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Appendix A — Details of Processing</div>

      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        <strong>Subject matter:</strong> Processing of Personal Data to provide Workplace.io culture and performance analytics and related features.<br><br>

        <strong>Duration:</strong> For the term of the Agreement, plus retention periods described in the Service and Customer instructions, and as required by law.<br><br>

        <strong>Nature and purpose:</strong> Hosting, ingestion, processing, and analysis of customer-authorized collaboration signals to generate aggregate reporting and trends; security, reliability, and support.<br><br>

        <strong>Categories of data subjects:</strong> Customer’s authorized users and members of Customer’s connected collaboration platforms.<br><br>

        <strong>Categories of Personal Data:</strong> May include identifiers (name, email, user IDs), workspace/channel identifiers, message-related metadata, and short-lived message content during processing; derived metadata and aggregated results used for reporting.<br><br>

        <strong>Special categories:</strong> The Service is not intended for processing special categories of personal data. Customer should avoid sending sensitive personal data in free-form inputs (including chat prompts) and should configure the Service consistent with internal policies.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================= -->
    <!-- APPENDIX B: Security Measures -->
    <!-- ============================= -->
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Appendix B — Security Measures</div>

      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Company maintains technical and organizational measures designed to protect Personal Data processed under this DPA. Measures include:
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Access control:</strong> workspace membership and roles restrict access to administrative functions; internal access restricted by least privilege.</li>
        <li><strong>Encryption in transit:</strong> TLS for communications between clients, providers, and services.</li>
        <li><strong>Encryption at rest:</strong> encrypted storage in hosting environments; restricted handling of integration credentials.</li>
        <li><strong>Logging and monitoring:</strong> operational monitoring and security-relevant logging with minimization of sensitive content in logs.</li>
        <li><strong>Incident response:</strong> defined process for detection, triage, containment, remediation, and communication.</li>
        <li><strong>Vendor management:</strong> subprocessor inventory and vendor risk practices; change management for vendors where applicable.</li>
        <li><strong>Secure development:</strong> review, testing, dependency hygiene, and controlled releases.</li>
        <li><strong>Data minimization:</strong> message content processed briefly then removed; derived metadata and aggregates retained for reporting.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Security Overview →", trust_doc_path("security-overview"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Encryption →", trust_doc_path("encryption"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Logging & Monitoring →", trust_doc_path("logging-monitoring"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================= -->
    <!-- APPENDIX C: Subprocessors -->
    <!-- ============================= -->
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Appendix C — Subprocessors</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        The current list of Subprocessors is maintained at:
        <%= link_to "Subprocessors", trust_doc_path("subprocessors"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>.
        Customer may request formal notice terms via written agreement.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================= -->
    <!-- APPENDIX D: SCCs (if applicable) -->
    <!-- ============================= -->
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Appendix D — Standard Contractual Clauses (if applicable)</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Where required for international transfers, SCCs will be incorporated by reference or executed between the parties, with appropriate module
        selections based on the parties’ roles. Customer may request SCCs by contacting:
        <a class="trust-doc-link" href="mailto:security@workplace.io">security@workplace.io</a>.
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "International Transfers (SCCs) →", trust_doc_path("scc"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-footer">
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-title">Need this as a downloadable PDF?</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-text">
        Contact us and we can provide a signature-ready version.
      </div>
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-actions">
        <%= link_to "Contact Trust & Security", trust_doc_path("contact"), class: "trust-doc-button" %>
        <%= link_to "Back to Trust Center", trust_center_path, class: "trust-doc-button trust-doc-button--secondary" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
